OL,3,CDrug deaths in Dumfries and Galloway
OL,4,Cincrease by 100%
OL,6,FNew figures show drug deaths in
OL,7,FDumfries and Galloway increased by 100
OL,8,Fper cent last year, despite numbers
OL,9,Facross Scotland dropping to their
OL,10,Flowest level in eight years.
OL,12,FTwenty-four people died from drug-
OL,13,Frelated causes in Dumfries and
OL,14,FGalloway in 2024, compared to 12 the
OL,15,Fyear before. Figures in the Scottish
OL,16,FBorders decreased from 11 deaths in
OL,17,F2023 to seven last year.
OL,19,FChair of the Drug-Related Deaths Group
OL,20,FChris Allan says each number
OL,21,F"represents another lost life".
